<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 15 at 5:16PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central
Broadwater and south central Meagher Counties through 545 PM MDT...
At 516 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles southwest of White Sulphur Springs, moving east at 35 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
White Sulphur Springs.
This includes the following highways...
Highway 12 between mile markers 20 and 44.
Highway 89 between mile markers 48 and 57.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
